    "answers": [
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Eu3PI.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 10732579,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 7898202,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/7898202/morgans42",
                "reputation": 687,
                "display_name": "MorganS42"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
            "score": 4,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1689385725,
            "creation_date": 1689385725,
            "body": "<p>Simple Answer: It's convenient.<\/p>\n<p>There are many times when we use the <code>.set()<\/code> method on an <code>ArrayList<\/code> when we still want to store the old value. If this functionality did not exist it would mean writing an extra line (and programmers hate writing extra lines when it is just as readable not to). Consider the scenario of having a list of shapes, but we sometimes want to replace old shapes with new shapes, when we do this we want to print out the old shape, without the <code>return<\/code> on the <code>.set()<\/code> we would have to do it like this:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>List&lt;Shape&gt; shapes = new ArrayList&lt;Shape&gt;();\n\n* populate the list *\n\nint index = 3;\nShape oldShape = shapes.get(index);\nShape newShape = new Shape(&quot;Pentagon&quot;);\n\nshapes.set(index, newShape);\nSystem.out.println(oldShape);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n<p>With the <code>return<\/code> it allows us to concisely do this:<\/p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>List&lt;Shape&gt; shapes = new ArrayList&lt;Shape&gt;();\n\n* populate the list *\n\nShape newShape = new Shape(&quot;Pentagon&quot;);\nSystem.out.println(shapes.set(3, newShape));\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 76691924,
            "question_id": 76691893
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/SdIqA.png?s=256",
                "account_id": 43022,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 125562,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/125562/basilevs",
